# Credit Card Fraud Detection

A simple machine learning project to detect fraudulent transactions from a highly imbalanced dataset.

---

## What this project does

Builds and compares models to identify fraud, where fraudulent cases are extremely rare (~0.17%).

---

## Dataset

* 284,807 transactions
* 492 fraud cases
* Features are anonymized (V1–V28) + Time, Amount

---

## Approach

* Basic data exploration
* Feature scaling
* Handling class imbalance
* Training multiple models

---

## Models used

* Logistic Regression
* Decision Tree
* Random Forest

---

## Evaluation

Accuracy is misleading here, so the focus is on:

* Recall
* Precision
* F1 Score
* ROC-AUC

---

## Key takeaway

Catching fraud is more important than overall accuracy, and handling imbalance is critical.

